Definition.WordDefinition:
Asymmetric \As`ym*met"ric\, Asymmetrical \As`ym*met"ri*cal\, a. [See {Asymmetrous}.] 1. Incommensurable. [Obs.] [1913 Webster]
2. Not symmetrical; wanting proportion; esp., not bilaterally symmetrical. --Huxley. [1913 Webster]

asymmetrical adj 1: characterized by asymmetry in the spatial arrangement or placement of parts or components [syn: {asymmetric}] [ant: {symmetrical}] 2: irregular in shape or outline; "asymmetrical features"; "a dress with an crooked hemline" [syn: {crooked}]
